Build an Android app called **WBNoti** (package `com.wbnoti`, version 0.18, versionCode 9). The app buzzes a WHOOP 4.0 or 5.0 fitness band over BLE when the phone receives notifications. It has no server backend — everything runs on-device.

---

## Project structure

```
settings.gradle.kts        → rootProject.name = "WhoopNoti", include(":app")
build.gradle.kts           → root, applies plugins (android.application, kotlin.android, kotlin.compose) with apply false
gradle.properties          → android.useAndroidX=true, android.enableJetifier=true, org.gradle.jvmargs=-Xmx2048m
app/build.gradle.kts       → see below
gradle/libs.versions.toml  → see below
app/proguard-rules.pro     → see below
```

