## `MainActivity.kt`

Jetpack Compose UI. Dark theme only (`darkColorScheme()`).

**`MainViewModel`** (`AndroidViewModel`):
- StateFlows for all prefs (calls, SMS, WhatsApp, Slack, Calendar enabled/buzzCount, smsFilter, whatsappFilter, slackFilter, enabledPackages, pinnedPackages, pinnedPackageCounts)
- `installedApps: StateFlow<List<Pair<String,String>>>` — loaded on `Dispatchers.IO` at init, sorted by label, excludes the app's own package + all built-in packages + a few Samsung system apps (`com.samsung.android.keyscafe`, `com.samsung.android.app.routineplus`)
- Setter functions launch coroutines to write prefs

**`WBNotiApp` composable** (main screen, `LazyColumn`):
1. App title + version name from `PackageManager`
2. Error card if notification access not granted → "Grant Access" button → `Settings.ACTION_NOTIFICATION_LISTENER_SETTINGS`
3. Error card if accessibility access not granted → `Settings.ACTION_ACCESSIBILITY_SETTINGS`
4. WHOOP connection card: shows state text (Disconnected / Scanning / Connecting / Connected), battery % (colour-coded: red ≤20%, amber ≤40%), Connect/Disconnect button or spinner
5. "Test Buzz" full-width button (only when READY)
6. **Notification Types** section heading
7. `BuzzCountRow` for: Phone Calls, SMS (with filter), WhatsApp (with filter), Slack (with filter), Google Calendar Meetings
8. Pinned apps as `BuzzCountRow` with a `×` remove button
9. **Apps** section heading
10. Per-app rows: label, `↑` pin button, toggle switch

`DisposableEffect` on lifecycle re-checks notification/accessibility grant on `ON_RESUME`.

**`BuzzCountRow` composable**:
- Card containing: label row (optional `×` remove button, optional `Test` button, toggle switch), buzz count stepper (− / count / +, range 1–10), optional `OutlinedTextField` keyword filter (label "Keyword filter", placeholder "all notifications", `singleLine = true`)

**`ToggleRow` composable**: simple card with label, optional Test button, toggle.

**`getInstalledUserApps`**: queries `ACTION_MAIN / CATEGORY_LAUNCHER`, deduplicates by package, excludes built-in packages, sorts by app label. Annotated `@SuppressLint("QueryAllPackages")`.

**`isNotificationAccessGranted`** / **`isAccessibilityGranted`**: check `Settings.Secure` strings by splitting on `:` and comparing `ComponentName.packageName`.

